## Summary

Implements **MVP 1: Basic App Shell with Header and Routing** as specified in the MVP plan.

This PR establishes the foundational app structure with a header component and routing setup for the OhMyDoc application.

## Changes

### AppHeader Component
- Created `components/AppHeader.vue` using @nuxt/ui UContainer
- Displays "OhMyDoc" app title prominently
- Includes empty left action slot for Format, Clear, Import buttons (MVP 8)
- Includes empty right action slot for Export and Zoom buttons (MVPs 7 & 9)
- Responsive design with dark mode support following @nuxt/ui design system

### Routing Structure
- Moved `app.vue` to root for proper pages/ directory support in Nuxt 4
- Created `pages/index.vue` as main landing page with navigation
- Created `pages/debug/` directory for component isolation demos
- Created `pages/debug/parser.vue` placeholder for MVP 2 XML parser testing
- Configured Nuxt.js file-based routing to recognize `/debug/*` pattern

### ESLint Configuration
- Updated `eslint.config.mjs` to exclude single-word page component names
- Added exceptions for `index` and `parser` pages (Nuxt file-based routing requirement)

### Testing
- Added Playwright test suite (`tests/mvp1-app-shell.spec.ts`)
- Tests verify app loading, header display, and navigation functionality
- Linting passes without errors

## Acceptance Criteria Met

✅ App loads without errors  
✅ AppHeader displays with app title and empty action slots  
✅ Can navigate to /debug/parser (even if empty)  
✅ @nuxt/ui components render correctly  
✅ Development server runs successfully on port 3002  
✅ Routing transitions work smoothly  

## Testing

Run the following commands to verify:

```bash
npm run lint          # Verify code quality
npm run dev           # Start dev server at http://localhost:3002
```

Navigate to:
- http://localhost:3002/ (Home page with navigation)
- http://localhost:3002/debug/parser (Debug page placeholder)

All subtasks completed:
- ✅ 1.1: Verified project structure and @nuxt/ui configuration
- ✅ 1.2: Created AppHeader component with empty action slots
- ✅ 1.3: Configured routing and created debug directory structure

\
Great work on implementing MVP 1! This is a solid foundation for the OhMyDoc application. Below is my detailed review:\
\
### ✅ Strengths\

1. **Clean Architecture**\

   - Follows Nuxt 4 best practices by moving `app.vue` to root directory\
   - File-based routing is properly configured with pages directory structure\
\
2. **@nuxt/ui Integration**\
   - Excellent use of @nuxt/ui components (UContainer, UButton, UCard, UAlert)\
   - Consistent styling with dark mode support throughout\
   - Proper semantic HTML with accessibility in mind\
\
3. **Well-Designed Future-Proofing**\
   - Named slots (`left-actions`, `right-actions`) in AppHeader are perfectly positioned for future button implementations\
   - Clear comments indicate which MVP will populate each slot\
   - Debug page structure ready for component isolation testing\
\
4. **Testing Coverage**\
   - Comprehensive Playwright test suite covering all acceptance criteria\
   - Tests verify routing, header display, and navigation flows\
   - Good use of descriptive test names\

5. **Documentation**\
   - Excellent in-code comments explaining purpose and future usage\
   - Task Master integration with detailed implementation notes\
   - Clear PR description with acceptance criteria checklist\
\
### 🔍 Observations \\u0026 Suggestions\
\
#### 1. **ESLint Configuration** (`eslint.config.mjs:9-10`)\
The ESLint rule configuration looks good, but consider scaling it for future debug pages:\
\
```javascript\
\'vue/multi-word-component-names\': [\'error\', {\
  ignores: [\'index\', \'parser\']  // Will need to update as more debug pages are added\
}]\
```\
\
**Suggestion**: You might want to add a comment indicating this list will grow, or consider using a pattern-based approach if ESLint supports it for the pages directory.\
\
#### 2. **AppHeader Component** (`components/AppHeader.vue:10-12`)\
The header title is hardcoded. While this is fine for MVP 1, consider future extensibility:\
\
```vue\
\\u003ch1 class=\\"text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white\\"\\u003e\
  OhMyDoc\
\\u003c/h1\\u003e\
```\
\
**Suggestion**: For later MVPs, you might want to make the title a prop with a default value for easier testing and potential white-labeling. Not necessary now, but keep in mind.\
\
#### 3. **Test Hardcoded Port** (`tests/mvp1-app-shell.spec.ts:5,12,20,33,43`)\
All tests use hardcoded `http://localhost:3002/`:\
\
**Suggestion**: Consider extracting the base URL to a constant or using Playwright\'s `baseURL` configuration in `playwright.config.ts` for easier environment switching:\
\
```typescript\
const BASE_URL = process.env.BASE_URL || \'http://localhost:3002\';\
```\
\
#### 4. **app.vue Structure** (`app.vue:2-6`)\
Simple and clean, but the wrapper div may be unnecessary:\
\
```vue\
\\u003ctemplate\\u003e\
  \\u003cdiv\\u003e\
    \\u003cNuxtRouteAnnouncer /\\u003e\
    \\u003cAppHeader /\\u003e\
    \\u003cNuxtPage /\\u003e\
  \\u003c/div\\u003e\
\\u003c/template\\u003e\
```\
\
**Question**: Is the wrapper `\\u003cdiv\\u003e` needed, or could the template have multiple root elements? (In Vue 3, fragments are supported, but Nuxt may have specific requirements.)\
\
#### 5. **Missing TypeScript Definitions**\
The TypeScript usage is minimal (only in test file). While not required for MVP 1, future MVPs will need:\
- Props interfaces for components\
- Type definitions for composables\
- This is appropriately scoped for this MVP\

\
### Overall Assessment\
\
✅ **APPROVED** - This is a solid foundation for the project that successfully implements MVP 1 requirements. The code is clean, well-structured, and follows the project\'s architectural guidelines.\
\
---\
\
## Strengths\
\
### 1. **Excellent Architectural Adherence**\
- Correctly uses @nuxt/ui for application chrome (AppHeader, navigation) ✅\
- Properly separates app UI from future document templates ✅\
- Follows the established `/debug/*` pattern for component demos ✅\
- App structure aligns with Nuxt 4 best practices (root-level `app.vue`) ✅\
\
### 2. **Clean Component Design**\
The `AppHeader.vue` component is well-designed:\
- Simple, focused responsibility\
- Named slots (`left-actions`, `right-actions`) provide clear extension points\
- Dark mode support via Tailwind classes\
- Good inline documentation for future MVP references\
\
### 3. **Thoughtful ESLint Configuration**\
The ESLint rule exception for single-word component names is:\
- Justified (Nuxt file-based routing requirement)\
- Well-documented with inline comment\
- Scoped specifically to necessary pages (`index`, `parser`)\
\
### 4. **Good Test Coverage**\
Playwright tests cover:\
- Basic app loading ✅\
- Header rendering ✅\
- Navigation flows ✅\
- Structure validation ✅\
\
---\
\
## Issues \\u0026 Recommendations\
\
### 🔴 **Critical: Hardcoded Port in Tests**\
\
**Location**: `tests/mvp1-app-shell.spec.ts:5, 12, 20, 26, 33, 39, 43`\
\
**Issue**: The test suite hardcodes `http://localhost:3002/` which will fail in CI/CD or different environments.\
\
**Current**:\
```typescript\
await page.goto(\'http://localhost:3002/\');\
```\
\
**Recommended Fix**:\
```typescript\
// At the top of the test file\
const BASE_URL = process.env.BASE_URL || \'http://localhost:3002\';\
\
test(\'should load the app without errors\', async ({ page }) =\\u003e {\
  await page.goto(BASE_URL);\
  // ...\
});\
```\
\
**Alternative**: Use Playwright\'s `baseURL` configuration in `playwright.config.ts`:\
```typescript\
export default defineConfig({\
  use: {\
    baseURL: process.env.BASE_URL || \'http://localhost:3002\',\
  },\
});\
\
// Then in tests:\
await page.goto(\'/\');\
```\
\
---\
\
### 🟡 **Medium: Accessibility Concerns**\
\
**Location**: `components/AppHeader.vue:10`\
\
**Issue**: The `\\u003ch1\\u003e` should ideally include a `lang` attribute if internationalization is planned, and the app title should be semantically connected to the page structure.\
\
**Consideration**: Since this is an MVP and WCAG 2.1 Level AA is targeted (per `docs/DECISIONS.md`), consider:\
- Adding `aria-label` to action slot containers when they\'re populated\
- Ensuring the header has proper landmark role (likely automatic with semantic HTML)\
\
**Current approach is acceptable for MVP 1**, but keep accessibility in mind for MVP 7-9 when buttons are added.\
\
---\
\
### 🟡 **Medium: Test Robustness**\
\
**Location**: `tests/mvp1-app-shell.spec.ts:47`\
\
**Issue**: The last test (\\"should display empty action slots in header\\") uses a weak selector:\
```typescript\
const header = page.locator(\'h1:has-text(\\"OhMyDoc\\")\').locator(\'..\');\
await expect(header).toBeVisible();\
```\
\
**Problem**: `.locator(\'..\')` navigates to the parent element, which is fragile and doesn\'t actually verify the slot structure exists.\
\
**Recommended**:\
```typescript\
test(\'should display empty action slots in header\', async ({ page }) =\\u003e {\
  await page.goto(\'/\');\
  \
  // Verify the header structure exists with flex container\
  const headerContainer = page.locator(\'h1:has-text(\\"OhMyDoc\\")\').locator(\'xpath=ancestor::div[@class*=\\"flex\\"]\');\
  await expect(headerContainer).toBeVisible();\
  \
  // Verify both action slot containers exist (even if empty)\
  const actionSlots = headerContainer.locator(\'div.flex.items-center.gap-2\');\
  await expect(actionSlots).toHaveCount(2); // left and right slots\
});\
```\
\
---\
\
### 🟢 **Minor: TypeScript Opportunities**\
\
**Location**: `pages/index.vue:31-34`, `pages/debug/parser.vue:42-45`\
\
**Observation**: The `\\u003cscript setup lang=\\"ts\\"\\u003e` blocks only contain comments. While this is valid, consider:\
- Removing the script blocks entirely if there\'s no logic yet\
- OR adding basic page metadata using Nuxt\'s `definePageMeta()` for future-proofing:\
\
```typescript\
\\u003cscript setup lang=\\"ts\\"\\u003e\
definePageMeta({\
  title: \'OhMyDoc - Home\',\
  description: \'XML-to-HTML real-time transformer\'\
});\
\\u003c/script\\u003e\
```\
\
**Not critical for MVP 1**, but improves SEO and page metadata structure.\
\
---\
\
### 🟢 **Minor: CSS Consistency**\
\
**Location**: `components/AppHeader.vue:2`\
\
**Observation**: The component uses inline Tailwind classes. This is consistent with @nuxt/ui patterns, but consider extracting border colors to CSS variables if they\'ll be reused across multiple components:\
\
```vue\
\\u003cstyle scoped\\u003e\
:root {\
  --header-border: theme(\'colors.gray.200\');\
}\
.dark {\
  --header-border: theme(\'colors.gray.800\');\
}\
\\u003c/style\\u003e\
```\
\
**Current approach is fine for MVP 1** - this is more relevant when you have multiple templates in MVP 10-11.\
\
---\
\
### 🟢 **Minor: Task Master Integration**\
\
**Location**: `.taskmaster/tasks/tasks.json`\
\
**Observation**: The task status updates are well-documented with timestamped info blocks. Great practice! Consider also updating the Task Master after the PR is merged to mark task 1 as `done` (currently `review`).\
\

## Summary

Implements **MVP 1: Basic App Shell with Header and Routing** as specified in the MVP plan.

This PR establishes the foundational app structure with a header component and routing setup for the OhMyDoc application.

## Changes

### AppHeader Component
- Created `components/AppHeader.vue` using @nuxt/ui UContainer
- Displays "OhMyDoc" app title prominently
- Includes empty left action slot for Format, Clear, Import buttons (MVP 8)
- Includes empty right action slot for Export and Zoom buttons (MVPs 7 & 9)
- Responsive design with dark mode support following @nuxt/ui design system

### Routing Structure
- Moved `app.vue` to root for proper pages/ directory support in Nuxt 4
- Created `pages/index.vue` as main landing page with navigation
